<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss version="2.0"><channel><title>Conteúdo de fisl12 marcado com a tag "volunteers"</title><link>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12</link><description>Conteúdo de fisl12 marcado com a tag "volunteers"</description><item><title>Deadline for volunteers registration was postponed</title><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0032/4121/voluntarios.jpg1306247119" height="163" alt="Voluntarios" style="float: left; margin-top: 3px; margin-bottom: 3px; margin-left: 6px; margin-right: 6px;" width="244"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;There is still some time for those who wish to participate at fisl12 as volunteers. Open slots are available for various positions at fisl' organizing committee and also at the event's media converage. Being a volunteer means to follow closely one of the world's largest technology events, but also a huge responsability and a role to play inside the event's organization.&lt;br&gt;Those who are willing to work with us in the four days of the event, or even before, shall send a brief resumé to the e-mail &lt;strong&gt;voluntariosfisl12 AT softwarelivre DOT org&lt;/strong&gt; up to June, 12.&lt;br&gt;Each new fisl' edition is a result of work by more than a hundred volunteers. They are anonymous colaborators who provide some of their time to make the largest free software event in Latin America to happen. We are very aware of the importance of this colaboration and the amount of exchange that fisl creates. Some volunteers bring expertise, other bring workforce and enthusiasm and fisl retributes with rooms for idea-sharing and knowledge-gathering.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 May 2011 14:27:08 +0000</pubDate><link>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12/fisl12/noticias/deadline-for-volunteers-registration-was-postponed</link><guid>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12/fisl12/noticias/deadline-for-volunteers-registration-was-postponed</guid></item><item><title>Journalism undergraduates will be able to cover fisl12</title><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Working as a volunteer in the largest free software event in Latin America may be a great opportunity for professionals willing to join the workmarket or for those who wish to gather knowledge. Besides enriching their resumé, the media coverage of the event allows students to really feel the daily pressure of a real press room. fisl's communication team is in charge of writing stories for the website, interview for the Free Software Radio and report for the Free Software TV.&lt;br&gt;Inside the fisl fair, a press-room booth is assembled, where the plots are are discussed, produced and edited. Volunteers colaborate in the whole process, concluding with the publication of the video in TVSL website, the podcast in the SL Radio website, or the text in fisl's website. This year, for the first time, a team of volunteers will do media coverage for fisl's website, which last year reached 2 million page views. Audience in the TV and Radio were also  expressive: only during the event the Radio had 693 unique listeners and the two websites had almost 80.000 visits in the four days.&lt;br&gt;Gabriel Galli, 6º semester journalism student at PUCRS is a veteran in fisl coverage. He volunteered in the last two editions and is preparing for his third. "Work at fisl is very enriching, both to the point of view of communication and of the free software, an opportunity to get in contact with the greatest figures in the subject and also to learn how to use software", he says.&lt;br&gt;Those who are interested in volunteering in media coverage of fisl12 may write to voluntariosfisl12 AT softwarelivre DOT org &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0032/0542/cartaz-site.jpg1305317533" height="670" alt="Cartaz_site" width="474"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 13 May 2011 17:25:18 +0000</pubDate><link>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12/fisl12/noticias/journalism-undergraduates-will-be-able-to-cover-fisl12</link><guid>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12/fisl12/noticias/journalism-undergraduates-will-be-able-to-cover-fisl12</guid></item><item><title>Volunteers </title><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="long_text"&gt;&lt;span title="Cada nova edição do fisl é resultado do trabalho de mais de uma centenas de voluntários." style="background-color: #ffffff;"&gt;Each new edition of fisl is the work of over one hundred volunteers. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="São colaboradores anônimos que doam parte do seu tempo para fazer acontecer o maior evento de software livre da América Latina!" style="background-color: #ffffff;"&gt;They are anonymous contributors who give their time to make happen the largest free software event in Latin America! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="Nós sabemos a importância dessa colaboração eo valor dessa troca que o fisl promove." style="background-color: #ffffff;"&gt;We know the importance of collaboration and the value of this exchange that promotes fisl. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="Alguns voluntários trazem expertise outros mão-de-obra e entusiasmo eo fisl devolve com espaços para compartilhar ideias e absorver conhecimento." style="background-color: #ffffff;"&gt;Some volunteers bring expertise, some manpower and enthusiasm and fisl returns with spaces to share ideas and absorb knowledge. &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="Pra todas essas pessoas, que nos ajudam todos os anos, para aqueles que já foram voluntários em alguma edição do fisl, que estão trabalhando na organização do fisl12 ou que vão participar, queremos dizer que o fisl só acontece graças a vocês!" style="background-color: #ffffff;"&gt;To  all those people who help us every year, for those who have volunteered  in any edition of fisl, who are working in the organization of fisl12 or participate, we mean that fisl only happens because of you! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="E que se o fisl surge todos os anos renovado é graças à energia eo poder dessa grande comunidade software livre!" style="background-color: #ffffff;"&gt;And it appears fisl is renewed every year thanks to the energy and power of this great free software community! &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="Quer ser voluntário?"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Want to volunteer? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="Ser voluntário do fisl significa acompanhar os bastidores de um dos maiores eventos de tecnologia do mundo, mas também representa uma grande responsabilidade e um papel a cumprir dentro da organização do evento." style="background-color: #ffffff;"&gt;Being  a fisl volunteer means accompany the backstage of one of the biggest  technology events of the world, but also represents a great  responsibility and a role within the organization. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="Quem estiver disposto a pegar junto nos quarto dias do evento ou até mesmo antes, veja o que é preciso para se inscrever." style="background-color: #ffffff;"&gt;Anyone willing to get together untill the fourth day of the event or even before, see what you need to subscribe. &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="Requisitos"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="* ter idade acima de 16 anos"&gt;* Being over 16 years &lt;br&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="* ter conhecimentos de informática, se possível conhecimento em software livre" style="background-color: #ffffff;"&gt;* Have knowledge of computers, if possible knowledge in free software &lt;br&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="* ter conhecimento intermediário de inglês e/ou espanhol"&gt;* &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="* estar disponível durante todos os dias do fisl, das 8h às 19h"&gt;Be available every day of fisl&lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="Inscrição"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registration &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="Para se candidatar a uma vaga de voluntário do fisl12, responda a pergunta:"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="Envie a sua resposta juntamente com as informações abaixo para voluntariosfisl12@softwarelivre.org até o dia 09/05/2011"&gt;Send an e-mail with the information below to &lt;a href="mailto:voluntariosfisl12@softwarelivre.org"&gt;voluntariosfisl12@softwarelivre.org&lt;/a&gt; until the day June 12th &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="- nome completo"&gt;- Full name &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="- CPF"&gt;- CPF &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="- endereço completo"&gt;- Full address &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="- um breve currículo"&gt;- A brief curriculum &lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="Se você já foi voluntário do fisl em outras edições ou se gostaria de trabalhar em alguma área específica, informe isso também no e-mail."&gt;If you already volunteer fisl in other editions or would like to work in any particular area, tell that too in the email. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="A divulgação dos voluntários selecionados será feita a partir do dia 23/05 por e-mail juntamente para a convocação para uma reunião geral de voluntários."&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 01 Apr 2011 13:28:39 +0000</pubDate><link>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12/fisl12/volunteers</link><guid>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12/fisl12/volunteers</guid></item></channel></rss>